				\begin{document}$$ d_{{z^{2} }} $$\end{document}-shaped orbital and points towards the extrinsic CO ligand. An axial character of the extracted 13C hyperfine coupling (A1C in Table 2) supports this. Therefore, it is expected to find a strong coupling of the 13C atom of COext even if the 57Fe hyperfine coupling on the distal iron is quite small. In general, this agrees with the experimental findings. Nevertheless, the closest calculated hyperfine coupling of 29 MHz (oxSH–CO model in Table 3) is much larger than the one observed experimentally [Aiso (A1C) = 17.1 MHz; Table 2]. Therefore, we conclude that the calculated spin population on the distal iron is overestimated.
